.TH "alloc_wrb_handle" 9 "alloc_wrb_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_wrb_handle \- To allocate a wrb handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct wrb_handle *" alloc_wrb_handle
.BI "(struct beiscsi_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cid "  ","
.BI "struct hwi_wrb_context **pcontext "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The hba pointer
.IP "cid" 12
The cid to use for allocation
.IP "pcontext" 12
ptr to ptr to wrb context
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This happens under session_lock until submission to chip
